- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with heap-manipulating programs and their verification. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of invariants in program verification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a learning-based approach for automatically generating invariants. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the verification of programs, which can be relevant for security purposes.
